cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.SD

This paper proposes a novel approach for generating syntactically and semantically correct data for structured data with formal grammars and semantics, such as computer programs and molecular structures. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper focuses on deep generative models. The paper also mentions applications in programming language (cs.PL) and molecules, which suggest possible categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SD (Software Engineering and Programming Languages). Additionally, the paper introduces a syntax-directed approach, which may also fit into the category of cs.SE (Software Engineering).
